  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "On the Planet of Sorcerers in the wake of Prospero's burning, Ahzek Ahriman walks the Great Ocean of the warp beside his primarch Magnus the Red, hunting for any future in which the Thousand Sons survive. The flesh-change is again consuming his brothers, and Ahriman — chief Librarian, scholar, would-be saviour — is already turning the work over in his mind that will become the infamous Rubric. Captains Hathor Maat, Amon and Sobek attend, but the audio drama leans on quiet dialogue rather than spectacle: a study of a brilliant, doomed mind reaching for a cure that will cost more than the disease.",
